niagara.query_engine
Class ActiveQueryList

java.lang.Object
  niagara.query_engine.ActiveQueryList

public class ActiveQueryList
extends java.lang.Object

The ActiveQueryList class is used to store the queries that are active in the query engine. Objects of type QueryInfo are stored in this list. The public interface include the ability to add a query, remove a query and retrieve a query. Methods are synchronized because multiple threads may access the list.

addQueryInfo

public void addQueryInfo(int queryId,
                         QueryInfo queryInfo)
                  throws ActiveQueryList.QueryIdAlreadyPresentException
Adds a query info object to the active query list. The active query list should never have a query with the same id.

Parameters:
queryId - the id of the query to be added
queryInfo - the query information to add to the active list
Throws:
ActiveQueryList.QueryIdAlreadyPresentException - If a query with the same id is already present in the list
